<refnamediv>
<refname>rlenoise</refname>
<refpurpose>Add random noise to an image</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv xml:id='synopsis'>
<cmdsynopsis>
  <command>rlenoise</command>    
    <arg choice='opt'><arg choice='plain'>-n </arg><arg choice='plain'><replaceable>amount</replaceable></arg></arg>
    <arg choice='opt'><arg choice='plain'>-o </arg><arg choice='plain'><replaceable>outfile</replaceable></arg></arg>
    <arg choice='opt'><replaceable>infile</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 xml:id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para><emphasis remap='I'>Rlenoise</emphasis>
adds uniform random noise to an image.  The peak-to-peak amplitude of
the noise can be specified with the
<option>-n</option>
flag, the default value is 4.  This program may be
useful for trying to deal with quantization in an output device, if
you are able to trade spatial resolution for color resolution, and you
don't have a good characterization of the quantization function.</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 xml:id='options'><title>OPTIONS</title>
<variablelist remap='TP'>
  <varlistentry>
  <term><emphasis remap='I'>infile</emphasis></term>
  <listitem>
<para>The input will be read from this file, otherwise, input will
be taken from stdin.</para>
  </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>-o</option><replaceable> outfile</replaceable></term>
  <listitem>
<para>If specified, output will be written to this file, otherwise it will
go to stdout.</para>
  </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</refsect1>

